As Karl has pointed out,, If you have been refused when asked to fill that
style
 of HORIZONTAL tank,,, You are getting erroneous information!

 In Ontario, and all Of North America .. HORIZONTAL tanks are EXEMPT.

 If you want to replace your valve,, you need one that DOES NOT have the
OPD...
 as gravity can cause improper operation of this valve on a HORIZONTAL tank.

 no best before date
 no valve regulations


 But they must be safe,, and rust or dents are not acceptable... or leaking
 valves.

